   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Ministerstvo zahrani&#x10D;n&#xFD;ch vec&#xED; a eur&#xF3;pskych z&#xE1;le&#x17E;itost&#xED; SR</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ministry of Foreign and European Affairs of the Slovak Republic</narrative>
  </reporting-org>
  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Transfer of experience in the reform of state and public administration</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">Transfer sk&#xFA;senost&#xED; pri reforme &#x161;t&#xE1;tnej a verjnej spr&#xE1;vy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Due to the integration into the EU, Serbia must implement the reform of local government, increase its efficiency and availability. In Slovakia this reform is carried out as a project of ESO (effective, accountable and open government). Therefore, the Ministry of Interior establishes the MCC as the primary contact of physical and legal persons with the executive of the state. Visit the Client Centre in Bratislava will be an example for the establishment of a similar center in Serbia and a tool of avoiding corruption, which is widespread in Serbia.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SK">&lt;p&gt;Kv&#xF4;li integr&#xE1;cii do E&#xDA; Srbsko mus&#xED; realizova&#x165; aj reformu miestnej samospr&#xE1;vy, zv&#xFD;&#x161;i&#x165; jej efekt&#xED;vnos&#x165; a dostupnos&#x165;. Slovensko t&#xFA;to reformu vykon&#xE1;va ako projekt ESO (efekt&#xED;vna, spo&#x13E;ahliv&#xE1; &#xA0;a otvoren&#xE1; verejn&#xE1; spr&#xE1;va). Z toho d&#xF4;vodu ministerstvo vn&#xFA;tra SR zria&#x10F;uje klientske centr&#xE1;, ako miesta prv&#xE9;ho kontaktu fyzick&#xFD;ch a pr&#xE1;vnych os&#xF4;b s v&#xFD;konnou mocou &#x161;t&#xE1;tu. N&#xE1;v&#x161;teva Klientskeho centra v Bratislave bude pr&#xED;kladom pre zriadenie podobn&#xE9;ho centra v Srbsku a prostriedkom ako sa vyhn&#xFA;&#x165; korupcii, ktor&#xE1; je v Srbsku ve&#x13E;mi roz&#x161;&#xED;ren&#xE1;.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
